[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has an above-minimum strength hand with a good 6-card suit. He opens 1\H.

WEST, with 9 points, is a little too weak to bid at the 2-level so she bids a catchall 1NT.

EAST shows his 6-card suit and extra strength by jumping to 3\H, which 
WEST raises to 4\H since two trumps is now adequate support.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "S:KQ74.83.762.AKQ2 92.KT2.AT9.J9854 JT83.AQ74.J53.76 A65.J965.KQ84.T3"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1C pass 1H pass 1S pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "489bc33421817defb352efc87e6c50b30fdde9ae6060537632abe850bdc22f19"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 14 points and opens her 4-card \C suit.

NORTH must respond, and with two 4-card Majors bids them "up-the-line", saying 1\H.

SOUTH now shows his 4-card \S suit, and NORTH again must bid. Since NORTH is pretty weak he just 
raises to 2\S, which SOUTH happily passes.}

